# Intuition
The intuition to solving this problem is to use a sliding window of size k. Count the number of vowels in the initial window, then subtract and vowels that fall outside of the window each iteration and add any new vowels that come into the window.

# Approach
There are two ways I solved this problem. One is more simple to think about and one is faster. The more simple to think about version is to create a hash set that contains all vowel letters. Each iteration check if `s[i]` is in the hash set, if it is add it to the running total. On each iteration after the first `k` iterations check `s[i-k]` to see if it is in the set. If it is in the set subtract `1` from the running total.
The improved version to this is the same approach, but to use a bitmask to check if the current `char` is a vowel instead of looking it up in the hash set. This improves runtime marginally (it has the same time complexity) since computers are much better at performing bitwise operations.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
*O(n)*

- Space complexity:
*O(1)*

# Code
## Hashset solution
```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maxVowels(string s, int k) {
        unordered_set<char> vowels = {'a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u'};
        int max_total = 0;
        int running_total = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); ++i) {
            running_total += vowels.find(s[i]) != vowels.end() ? 1 : 0;
            if (i - k >= 0) {
                running_total -= vowels.find(s[i - k]) != vowels.end() ? 1 : 0;
            }
            max_total = max(max_total, running_total);
        }
        return max_total;
    }
};
```

## Bitwise solution
```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maxVowels(string s, int k) {
        auto is_vowel = [](char c) {
            static const uint32_t b1 = 0x208222;
            static const uint8_t b2 = 0x1f;
            static const uint8_t b3 = 0x1;
            return (b1 >> (c & b2)) & b3; 
        };
        int running_total = 0;
        int max_total = 0;
        for(int i = 0, j = i - k; i < s.size(); ++i, ++j){
            running_total += is_vowel(s[i]);
            if (i >= k) {
                running_total -= is_vowel(s[j]);
            }
            max_total = max(max_total, running_total); 
        }

        return max_total;
    };
};
```

